In a press conference at 10:59 A.M. EST, President Biden expressed gratitude to Speaker Pelosi and those who supported the American Rescue Plan, which passed in the House of Representatives. He highlighted that this plan brings the nation closer to achieving widespread vaccination, providing $1,400 in direct payments to Americans, extending unemployment benefits, assisting families with food and housing, and reopening schools safely. The President emphasized the urgency of swift action in the Senate to address the ongoing impact of the pandemic. He stated that the American Rescue Plan aims to alleviate the suffering experienced by the American people and revive the economy.